value:
Sketches and incipits mostly related to concerti grossi op. 6 and the Ode for St Cecilia's day.
Probably originally joined to leaf p. 63-64, q.v. The top and right hand side of both pages are heavily stained, with some show through.
Holograph manuscript in ink.
Watermark: Fleur de lis over Strasbourg bend; countermark: "IV" (Burrows B140)

p. 61, lines 1-2. [Sketch 1 : 8 bars, treble and bass clefs, G major]
